ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | ax12v2.1 | |- ( x = z -> ( ph -> A. x ( x = z -> ph ) ) ) |
| 2 |  | #P_ax6ev | |- E. z z = y |
| 3 |  | #P_equequ2 | |- ( z = y -> ( x = z <-> x = y ) ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_adantl | |- ( ( -. A. x x = y /\ z = y ) -> ( x = z <-> x = y ) ) |
| 5 |  | #P_dveeq2 | |- ( -. A. x x = y -> ( z = y -> A. x z = y ) ) |
| 6 | 5 | #P_imp | |- ( ( -. A. x x = y /\ z = y ) -> A. x z = y ) |
| 7 |  | #P_nfa1 | |- F/ x A. x z = y |
| 8 | 3 | #P_imbi1d | |- ( z = y -> ( ( x = z -> ph ) <-> ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) |
| 9 | 8 | #P_sps | |- ( A. x z = y -> ( ( x = z -> ph ) <-> ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) |
| 10 | 7, 9 | #P_albid | |- ( A. x z = y -> ( A. x ( x = z -> ph ) <-> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) |
| 11 | 6, 10 | #P_syl | |- ( ( -. A. x x = y /\ z = y ) -> ( A. x ( x = z -> ph ) <-> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) |
| 12 | 11 | #P_imbi2d | |- ( ( -. A. x x = y /\ z = y ) -> ( ( ph -> A. x ( x = z -> ph ) ) <-> ( ph -> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) ) |
| 13 | 4, 12 | #P_imbi12d | |- ( ( -. A. x x = y /\ z = y ) -> ( ( x = z -> ( ph -> A. x ( x = z -> ph ) ) ) <-> ( x = y -> ( ph -> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) ) ) |
| 14 | 1, 13 | #P_mpbii | |- ( ( -. A. x x = y /\ z = y ) -> ( x = y -> ( ph -> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) ) |
| 15 | 14 | #P_ex | |- ( -. A. x x = y -> ( z = y -> ( x = y -> ( ph -> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) ) ) |
| 16 | 15 | #P_exlimdv | |- ( -. A. x x = y -> ( E. z z = y -> ( x = y -> ( ph -> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) ) ) |
| 17 | 2, 16 | #P_mpi | |- ( -. A. x x = y -> ( x = y -> ( ph -> A. x ( x = y -> ph ) ) ) ) |
\
 Recovery of ~ ax-c15 from ~ ax12v without using ~ ax-c15 .  The hypothesis is even weaker than ~ ax12v , with ` z ` both distinct from ` x ` _and_ not occurring in ` ph ` .  Thus, the hypothesis provides an alternate axiom that can be used in place of ~ ax-c15 .  (Contributed by NM, 2-Feb-2007.)  (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)
